-- Moore Capital Buys Stake in U.K.’s Metro Bank, Sky News Says
-- B y   J a s o n   W e b b
-- 2012-05-26T10:31:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-26/moore-capital-buys-stake-in-u-k-s-metro-bank-sky-news-says.html
Hedge fund  Moore Capital  has bought a
stake in the U.K.’s Metro Bank, Sky News’ Mark Kleinman reported
on his  blog .  Moore Capital bought the stake as part of a 125 million
pound ($196 million) fundraising by the bank, Kleinman said.  Existing Metro shareholders, including billionaires David
and Simon Reuben, the U.K.’s McAlpine family and LeFrak
Organization Inc., a U.S. property company, also participated in
the fundraising, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Webb in London at 
 jwebb25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  